  "prompt": "Which is the best website for online study of mechanical engineering?",
  "response": "There are several excellent websites for studying mechanical engineering online, each offering a variety of resources. Some of the best include:\n\n1. **Coursera** - Provides courses from top universities and companies, including mechanical engineering topics.\n2. **edX** - Offers courses from universities like MIT and Harvard, with many options in mechanical engineering.\n3. **MIT OpenCourseWare** - Provides free access to course materials from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, including mechanical engineering.\n4. **Khan Academy** - Features tutorials and practice exercises in various subjects, including some relevant to mechanical engineering.\n5. **Udemy** - Offers a wide range of courses, including many focused on different aspects of mechanical engineering.\n6. **YouTube** - Channels like Learn Engineering and NPTEL provide quality educational videos on mechanical engineering concepts.\n7. **Engineering.com** - Offers articles, tutorials, and other resources related to mechanical engineering.\n\nChoosing the best website depends on your specific needs, such as the depth of content, format, and whether you prefer free or paid resources.",
